						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 90 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of <hi rend="bold">Śirutaḷikkōyil-Mahādēva</hi> at Uṟumūr a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> and <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Nalvayalūr-kūṟṟam on the north bank (of the river), by a lady named <hi rend="bold">Pichchaiyaṉ Āruvaṅgi.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
